  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the stem off your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s] </strong>and deseed (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) then cut a slit down the middle, lengthways (don't cut the whole way through!)</p><p>Add the<strong> cut pepper[s]</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), cut-side down, with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up, then put the tray[s] in the oven and cook for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684231568433-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684231568433-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684231568433-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684231568433-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1684231568433-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large pot with a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the rice is fully coated</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684231811866-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684231811866-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684231811866-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684231811866-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684231811866-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is fully coated, add 250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684232003549-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684232003549-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684232003549-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684232003549-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684232003549-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong>, then crumble your <strong>Greek cheese</strong> into small bite-sized pieces in a bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped green chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>half</strong> the<strong> drained sweetcorn</strong> (save the rest for later!) to the bowl with the <strong>cornflour</strong> and <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Greek cheese filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684232033639-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684232033639-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684232033639-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684232033639-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684232033639-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the initial 15 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Flip the <strong>pepper[s] </strong>over and stuff with the <strong>Greek cheese filling</strong> (be careful, it will be hot!)</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 10 min further or until the filling is slightly charred and the pepper is completely softened – this is your <strong>chilli cheese-stuffed pepper[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684232039714-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684232039714-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684232039714-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684232039714-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684232039714-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pepper is cooking, save some <strong>coriander leaves</strong> for garnish, then chop the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> in a small bowl with a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> coriander yoghurt</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684232044510-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684232044510-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684232044510-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684232044510-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684232044510-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>remaining sweetcorn</strong> and mix it all together – this is your <strong>buttery red rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684232050637-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684232050637-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684232050637-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684232050637-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684232050637-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>buttery red rice</strong> with the <strong>chilli cheese-stuffed pepper </strong>on top</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>coriander yoghurt </strong>and garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
